description:
&lt;p&gt;Aneurin Bevan University Health Board are committed to delivering quality services based on the needs of the people who use them. As a Peer Mentor Development Worker, you will be an ambassador of Peer Mentoring for the Health Board, working within a multi-disciplinary team to improve the understanding of peer support across ABUHB. You will support the ongoing development of a variety of Peer Mentor roles across the Health Board, to include aspects of training, supervision and the development of new opportunities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are pleased to be offering two part time Peer Mentor Development Worker positions within Adult Mental Health Services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The roles will include some administrative duties.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to being community services, the ability to travel between sites is essential to this post.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note: There are two part time posts available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 8th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mel Glover, Deputy Directorate Manager - 01495 765798&lt;/p&gt;
